{"category":"grounding","question":"How long does my child need to be fever-free before returning?","response":{"answer":"Your child needs to be fever-free for 24 hours without medication before returning to Sunflower. So if they had a fever today, they'd be ready to come back the day after tomorrow, as long as they haven't needed fever-reducing medicine during that full 24-hour window.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["illness-policy"],"directly_addressed_by":["illness-policy"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What's the teacher-to-child ratio in the infant room?","response":{"answer":"In the infant room, we keep a ratio of 1 teacher for every 4 children, with a maximum group size of 8. This means your baby gets plenty of individual attention throughout the day.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["ratios"],"directly_addressed_by":["ratios"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What curriculum do you use?","response":{"answer":"Sunflower uses a blend of Reggio Emilia-inspired project work and Creative Curriculum for Preschool. That means your child's interests shape the week — if the classroom is fascinated by ants, we'll spend a week on ants, with books, art, dramatic play, and an outdoor magnifying-glass hunt. We track each child's development with ongoing observational notes and the Ages and Stages Questionnaire (ASQ-3), which we share with you at parent-teacher conferences. Our goal is to send children to kindergarten curious, confident, and loved — not ready for a standardized test.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["curriculum"],"directly_addressed_by":["curriculum"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"How do you track my child's development?","response":{"answer":"We track your child's development through ongoing observational notes that teachers keep throughout the day, and we also use the Ages and Stages Questionnaire (ASQ-3), which is a standardized screening tool. We share these observations and results with you at each parent-teacher conference — we hold those twice a year, in the fall and spring. Outside of conferences, you can request a meeting with your child's teacher anytime by messaging through the family app if you have questions or concerns about their progress.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["curriculum","conferences"],"directly_addressed_by":["curriculum"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"Can my child bring peanut butter sandwiches?","response":{"answer":"No, peanut butter isn't allowed at Sunflower. We're a peanut- and tree-nut-free building — we don't make exceptions, even for packed lunches or birthday treats. This keeps all our children safe, especially those with nut allergies. Our kitchen team is happy to help you think through nut-free lunch ideas if you'd like — just reach out to your child's teacher or call the office at (512) 555-0142.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["food-allergies"],"directly_addressed_by":["food-allergies"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"How much is toddler tuition?","response":{"answer":"Toddler tuition at Sunflower is $1,560 per month. That includes meals, snacks, diapers, and all classroom materials — there are no extra supply fees during the year. If you have more than one child enrolled, the younger child gets a 10% sibling discount.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["tuition"],"directly_addressed_by":["tuition"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"How much is Twos tuition?","response":{"answer":"Twos tuition is $1,470 per month. That includes meals, snacks, diapers, and all classroom materials — there are no extra supply fees during the year. If you have more than one child enrolled, the younger child gets a 10% sibling discount.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["tuition"],"directly_addressed_by":["tuition"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"Is there a supply fee?","response":{"answer":"Yes, there's an annual supply fee of $120 per child, charged each August. It covers art materials, classroom books, and outdoor program equipment for the year. There's also a one-time registration fee of $150 when you enroll. Both fees are non-refundable after your child's first day.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["registration-fee"],"directly_addressed_by":["registration-fee"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What's the late tuition fee?","response":{"answer":"A late payment fee of $35 is added to your bill if tuition isn't paid by the 5th of the month. Tuition is due on the 1st, so you have a few days of grace. If you're ever in a tight spot, reach out to Director Maya directly — we've worked out payment plans with families before.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["tuition-due"],"directly_addressed_by":["tuition-due"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"Do you offer sibling discounts?","response":{"answer":"Yes, we do. If you have more than one child enrolled at Sunflower, the younger child receives a 10% discount on their monthly tuition.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["tuition"],"directly_addressed_by":["tuition"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What's the teacher-to-child ratio for toddlers?","response":{"answer":"For toddlers, we maintain a ratio of 1 teacher for every 6 children, with a maximum group size of 12. Every classroom has at least two teachers on the floor throughout the day.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["ratios"],"directly_addressed_by":["ratios"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What's the ratio in the twos classroom?","response":{"answer":"In the Twos classroom, we keep a ratio of 1 teacher for every 8 children, with a maximum group size of 16. We also make sure there are at least two teachers on the floor throughout the day — we never leave a single teacher alone with a group.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["ratios"],"directly_addressed_by":["ratios"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What's the teacher-to-child ratio for preschool?","response":{"answer":"For preschool, we keep a ratio of 1 teacher to 10 children, with a maximum group size of 20. We also make sure there are always at least two teachers on the floor throughout the day — we never leave a single teacher alone with a group.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["ratios"],"directly_addressed_by":["ratios"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What's the maximum group size in the infant room?","response":{"answer":"The maximum group size in the infant room is 8 children, with a teacher-to-child ratio of 1 to 4.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["ratios"],"directly_addressed_by":["ratios"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"When do you apply sunscreen?","response":{"answer":"We apply sunscreen to every child before outdoor time whenever the UV index is 3 or higher. Please bring in a labeled bottle of your child's preferred sunscreen (SPF 30 or higher is ideal) and sign the sunscreen permission form at enrollment — we can't apply it without your okay. We also seek shade whenever possible and encourage sun hats during outdoor play.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["sunscreen"],"directly_addressed_by":["sunscreen"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What are the operating hours?","response":{"answer":"Sunflower is open Monday through Friday from 7:00 am to 6:00 pm. We ask families to aim for drop-off by 9:30 am so children can settle into the morning routine with their friends. We're closed on weekends and on the holidays listed in your yearly calendar.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["hours"],"directly_addressed_by":["hours"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
{"category":"grounding","question":"What time should I drop off by?","response":{"answer":"We ask families to aim for drop-off by 9:30 am so your child can settle into the morning routine with their friends. Late arrivals miss breakfast and the opening circle, which are some of the warmest parts of the day.","confidence":"high","cited_entries":["hours"],"directly_addressed_by":["hours"],"escalate":false,"refusal":false}}
